<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I kept finding the need to conditionally issue SoapServer faults outside of the scope of classes or functions being handled by SoapServer.</p>

<p>To issue a SoapServer fault, you merely need to call SoapServer::fault($code, $message, ...), but from what I can deduce, Zend_Soap_Server has no public method to retrieve the instance of SoapServer it is using.</p>

<p>One fix is to make Zend_Soap_Server::_getSoap() a public method.  Alternatively, I chose to add an $issueFault flag to Zend_Soap_Server::fault().  By default, it will not issue a SoapServer fault, but if set to true, a fault will be issued with the message and code provided.</p>

<p>I have supplied the diff.</p>

<p>Please let me know if I'm off base in my attempt or am missing some simple way to externally issue a SoapServer fault through Zend_Soap_Server.</p>

